\par\par \uc2 Trilobites\par \uc2 Science\par {\*\bkmkstart toc1}{\*\bkmkend toc1}\b \uc2 How Do You Save Snow Leopards? First, Gather Their Droppings\b0\par\par\uc2 By NICHOLAS ST. FLEUR \par \uc2 747 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 February 2017\par 16:50\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 On the rocky cliffs of the Himalayas, the path to snow leopard conservation is paved in feces.\par \par \uc2 Their population decimated by poaching and habitat destruction, only about 4,000 of the endangered cats remain in the wild, according to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wwf.panda.org/what_we_do/endangered_species/snow_leopard/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 World Wildlife Fund}}}\uc2 . Conflicts with mountain farmers and pastoral herders also contribute to their dwindling numbers.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CThe problem is when a snow leopard gets inside a livestock pen,\u8221\'20\'1D said {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://hil-no.academia.edu/MadhuChetri"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Madhu Chetri}}}\uc2 , a biologist at Inland Norway \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Applied Sciences. When that happens, he said, the carnivore usually eats a handful of goats and sheep, but in some cases it can massacre more than 100 animals in a single corral.\par \par \uc2 If the cat gets stuck in a pen, the inevitable tends to occur. \u8220\'20\'1CThere is a high chance the herders will kill it in retaliation,\u8221\'20\'1D he said.\par \par \uc2 Dr. Chetri and his team are studying conflicts between humans and snow leopards in areas of Nepal in order to find ways to mitigate them. That\u8217\'20\'19s why they spent more than 150 days in the Central Himalayas sniffing out snow leopard scat. Embedded in the excrement were clues to decoding the cat\u8217\'20\'19s diet and determining how often it ate livestock, which could one day guide conservation strategies to reduce contact between snow leopards and farm animals. They published their findings Wednesday in the journal {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0170549"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 PLOS One}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 In addition to collecting snow leopard feces, the team also scooped up wolf droppings. Himalayan wolves are not nearly as threatened as their feline counterparts, but they are also an elusive mountain predator that meddles with livestock.\par \par \uc2 Dr. Chetri and his colleagues trekked along trails, mountain ridges, riverbeds and mountain passes collecting the predators\u8217\'20\'19 wastes. When they came across a pile, they placed a small piece into a plastic tube and a large chunk into a paper envelope. They performed DNA analysis on the pieces in the plastic tubes to determine whether they belonged to a snow leopard, wolf or some other carnivore, as well as to figure out if it was left by a male or a female. The researchers later examined the pieces in the envelopes for traces of fur to determine what the predator had eaten.\par \par \uc2 They collected more than 800 dung samples, but not every one was a winner. In a few cases they accidentally collected feces that belonged to a feral dog, a lynx or a brown bear. Among their fecal data set, they verified that 182 of their specimens belonged to snow leopards and 57 to wolves.\par \par \uc2 The researchers used water and mesh sieves to extract hair from the larger samples and manually took out bones, claws, feathers and plants. The team found that 27 percent of the snow leopard stool samples included domestic animals like horses and goats.\par \par \uc2 But by far the most popular animal that the spotted cats were dining on was the wild bharal, or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.tibetnature.net/en/blue-sheep/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Himalayan blue sheep}}}\uc2 . Traces of this big horned beast appeared in more than half of the samples. The researchers also found that livestock remains appeared in male droppings twice as often as in the specimens from females.\par \par \uc2 Dr. Chetri said that their findings would serve as the first step toward understanding how snow leopards affect the livestock of the rural peoples in the Himalayas. Their next steps are to determine the economic impact that the killings of farm animals have on the pasture herders, and then to develop strategies that will help reduce interactions between humans and the cats.\par \par \uc2 As the field work came to an end, Dr. Chetri experienced a frightening encounter.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1COn the last day the snow leopard spotted me thinking maybe I was a prey,\u8221\'20\'1D he said. As he was hiding in the cliffs, the cat crawled closer until it was about 10 feet away. \u8220\'20\'1CI was really scared and I had to turn over and show it, \u8216\'20\'18No, I\u8217\'20\'19m not prey, I\u8217\'20\'19m a human.\u8217\'20\'19\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://on.fb.me/1paTQ1h"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Like the Science Times page on Facebook.}}}\uc2  | Sign up for the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://nyti.ms/1MbHaRU"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  Science Times newsletter.}}}\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2011/07/26/science/26angier.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 A Forbidding Kingdom of Snow Leopards}}}\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/30/science/cheetahs-endangered-species.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Cheetahs in Danger of Extinction, Researchers Say}}}\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/06/science/endangered-species-trade-map.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Endangered Species and the Stuff We Buy, All Mapped Out}}}\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2015/07/31/movies/illuminating-the-plight-of-endangered-species-at-the-empire-state-building.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Illuminatin