\par\par \uc2 Fashion & Style\par {\*\bkmkstart toc2}{\*\bkmkend toc2}\b \uc2 Joe Biden Drops by a Fashion Show. The Reason? His Daughter.\b0\par\par\uc2 By VALERIYA SAFRONOVA \par \uc2 606 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 February 2017\par 16:42\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 Former Vice President {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/b/joseph_r_jr_biden/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Joseph R. Biden Jr.}}}\uc2  revealed on Tuesday that for his next act, he would be leading a new initiative at the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/organizations/u/university_of_pennsylvania/index.html?inline=nyt-org"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 \\b University\\b0  of Pennsylvania}}}\uc2  called the Penn Biden Center for Diplomacy and Global Engagement.\par \par \uc2 But before digging into his new job, Mr. Biden headed to a fashion party, where he turned out be the star guest.\par \par \uc2 The occasion: the unveiling of a collection of hoodies designed by his daughter, Ashley Biden, the executive director of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dcjustice.org/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Delaware Center for Justice}}}\uc2 , together with the e-tailer Gilt. Proceeds from sales of the organic cotton, made-in-America hoodies ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.gilt.com/sale/women/livelihood?q.display=&q.start=11"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 sold on Gilt.com}}}\uc2  for $79 to $99) will go to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.getinvolvedinyourhood.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Livelihood}}}\uc2 , an organization Ms. Biden started along with the line to aid economic development in Wilmington, Del., and Anacostia, a neighborhood in Washington.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CSocial justice doesn\u8217\'20\'19t come from national movements or Washington politics; it comes from people making changes in their communities, in their day-to-day lives,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr. Biden said in an email. \u8220\'20\'1CIt comes from people demanding change and creating change, every single day.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Or wearing it, anyway.\par \par \uc2 Despite not being a typical fashionista, Mr. Biden nonetheless drew a huge crowd during the event at Spring Place in TriBeCa, putting his Secret Service detail \u8212\'20\'14 another unusual presence at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/subjects/n/new_york_fashion_week/index.html?inline=nyt-classifier"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 New York Fashion Week}}}\uc2  \u8212\'20\'14 on edge. He remained for a full hour and a half, posing with a seemingly endless line of fans, including preening models and a few photographers who briefly swapped their professional cameras for selfie-friendly iPhones.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Biden, it turns out, understands the impact clothes can have on society.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CYou get dressed every day,\u8221\'20\'1D he said. \u8220\'20\'1CIf you\u8217\'20\'19re using that opportunity to support your community and your neighbors, you\u8217\'20\'19re helping give people a fair shot to do something extraordinary with their lives.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 His influence is what led Ms. Biden to a career in social work.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIt started with my love of animals,\u8221\'20\'1D she said. \u8220\'20\'1CMy dad used to come home every night and I used to sit by the sink and talk to him about how we have to save these dolphins that were getting caught in tuna nets. He linked me up with then-Congresswoman Barbara Boxer, who I referred to as the dolphin lady, and she had me go onto the Congress floor and talk to Republican senators.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The Dolphin Protection Consumer Information Act was passed, and Ms. Biden had her first taste of public service.\par \par \uc2 Now, however, she has teamed up with some other influencers, including the designers Christian Siriano and Mara Hoffman and the socialite Olivia Palermo, who mingled at the party with assorted models, snacked on foie gras puffs and perused a rack of soft, cozy hoodies in black, navy, forest green, blush, cream and slate.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CObviously it\u8217\'20\'19s different from what I do, but they look cool,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr. Siriano said. \u8220\'20\'1CMe and my husband wouldn\u8217\'20\'19t be married without Joe. It\u8217\'20\'19s nice to kick off fashion week with something that feels good.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Though Mr. Biden was visibly glad to be supporting his daughter\u8217\'20\'19s collection, he was clearly somewhat amused at the situation.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CI know I\u8217\'20\'19m being used,\u8221\'20\'1D he said, referring to Ms. Biden, \u8220\'20\'1Cbut I don\u8217\'20\'19t mind.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Joseph R. Biden Jr. with his daughter, Ashley Biden, during a fashion event in New York unveiling Ms. Biden\u8217\'20\'19s hoodies collection. | Danny Ghitis for The New York Times | Mr. Biden posing with the models Hannah Smith, left, and Ella Rattigan at a fashion event in New York. | Danny Ghitis for The New York Times \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170208ed28008et\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
