\par\par \uc2 First 100 Days Briefing\par \uc2 U.S.; Politics\par {\*\bkmkstart toc3}{\*\bkmkend toc3}\b \uc2 Trump Says Nordstrom Treated His Daughter \u8216\'20\'18So Unfairly\u8217\'20\'19; Fireworks Before Final Vote on Jeff Sessions\b0\par\par\uc2 By RICHARD P\u201\'00\'C9REZ-PE\u209\'00\'D1A, DANA GOLDSTEIN, EMMARIE HUETTEMAN and MATT FLEGENHEIMER \par \uc2 1,787 \uc2 words\par \uc2 8 February 2017\par 04:00\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 \u9632\'25\'A0 A vote on Jeff Sessions\u8217\'20\'19s nomination as attorney general is expected on Wednesday.\par \par \uc2 \u9632\'25\'A0 A proposed Senate bill would require congressional approval to lift sanctions on Russia.\par \par \uc2 \u9632\'25\'A0 Vice President \uc2 Mike Pence\uc2  will attend a Republican Jewish Coalition meeting in Las Vegas.\par \par \uc2 Trump goes after another company, and this time it\u8217\'20\'19s personal\par \par \uc2 Mr. Trump on Wednesday lashed out at Nordstrom for dropping his daughter Ivanka\u8217\'20\'19s clothing and accessories line, once again raising questions about the tangled relationship between the president and his family\u8217\'20\'19s business interests.\par \par \uc2 My daughter Ivanka has been treated so unfairly by {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/Nordstrom"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 @Nordstrom}}}\uc2 . She is a great person -- always pushing me to do the right thing! Terrible! \u8212\'20\'14 \uc2 Donald J. Trump\uc2  (@realDonaldTrump) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/829356871848951809"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 February 8, 2017}}}\par \par \uc2 The president has been criticized for singling out other companies for criticism, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/21/business/donald-trump-boeing-lockheed.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 like Boeing and Lockheed Martin}}}\uc2 , prompting gyrations in their stock prices, but those controversies had to do with government contracts, not his family\u8217\'20\'19s own fortunes.\par \par \uc2 Nordstrom, the department store chain, said on Friday that it was {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bigstory.ap.org/article/19ae5b3f6808496f804b16111dcccd7c/nordstrom-drop-ivanka-trumps-clothing-accessories-line"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 dropping the Ivanka Trump line}}}\uc2 , a decision it said was based on sales performance. A campaign, using the hashtag #GrabYourWallet, which has encouraged shoppers to boycott products with ties to Mr. Trump, his family and his donors, called the Nordstrom announcement a victory.\par \par \uc2 It was not clear what prompted the president to criticize the company five days later. As Mr. Trump has noted several times, federal conflict-of-interest laws apply to other officials, but not to the president.\par \par \uc2 Nordstrom\u8217\'20\'19s stock dropped briefly after the president\u8217\'20\'19s \uc2 Twitter\uc2  post, then rose again.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s blast at the company came two days after his wife, Melania, filed a libel lawsuit describing her \u8220\'20\'1Cmultiyear term\u8221\'20\'1D as \u8220\'20\'1Cone of the most photographed women in the world\u8221\'20\'1D \u8212\'20\'14 an apparent reference to her status as a candidate\u8217\'20\'19s wife and now first lady \u8212\'20\'14 as a lucrative business opportunity.\par \par \uc2 DeVos brings along a sense of humor on her first day\par \par \uc2 A day after her narrow confirmation as education secretary, Betsy DeVos toured the department she now leads and delivered a speech to staff members and reporters.\par \par \uc2 She began with a joke: \u8220\'20\'1CThis confirmation process and the drama it engendered have been a bit of a bear,\u8221\'20\'1D she said, a reference to her much-lampooned comment during her Senate hearing that schools might need guns to protect students from \u8220\'20\'1Cgrizzlies.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWe\u8217\'20\'19ve just come through one of the most bruising, divisive elections in modern times, and that\u8217\'20\'19s O.K.,\u8221\'20\'1D she said. \u8220\'20\'1CAll of us here can help bring unity by personally committing to being more open to and patient toward views different from our own.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 In her speech, she did not mention some of the issues that had made her such a contentious nominee, like her support of private school vouchers and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/subjects/c/charter_schools/index.html?inline=nyt-classifier"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 charter schools}}}\uc2 . But while she had seemed unfamiliar in her Senate hearing with basic education terms and policies, such as the requirements of the Individuals With Disabilities Education Act, on Wednesday Ms. DeVos went out of her way to promise to serve \u8220\'20\'1Cspecial-needs students and families to whom we owe our full support,\u8221\'20\'1D as well as \u8220\'20\'1Cstudents who may be struggling\u8221\'20\'1D and \u8220\'20\'1Chardworking teachers who may feel stifled.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 She continued, \u8220\'20\'1CI pledge to listen and learn from you, and from stakeholders around our country.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The finish line is near on a rocky road to attorney general\par \par \uc2 Capping a strikingly contentious confirmation process, the Senate is expected to vote as soon as Wednesday evening on the nomination of Senator Jeff Sessions of Alabama to be attorney general.\par \par \uc2 Senators usually show a great deal of deference when one of their own is nominated for a cabinet post. But Democrats have sharply criticized over his background on civil rights and his stances on voter access and immigration.\par \par \uc2 After Mr. Sessions\u8217\'20\'19s nomination cleared a procedural hurdle on Tuesday in the Senate, Democrats took to the floor to reiterate their opposition to the senator during the final hourslong debate.\par \par \uc2 I will not be silent about a nominee for AG who has made derogatory & racist comments that have no place in our justice system. \u8212\'20\'14 Elizabeth Warren (@SenWarren) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/SenWarren/status/829140184692305923"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 February 8, 2017}}}\par \par \uc2 I will not be silent while the Republicans rubber stamp an AG who will never stand up to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/POTUS"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 @POTUS}}}\uc2  when he breaks the law. \u8212\'20\'14 Elizabeth Warren (@SenWarren) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/SenWarren/status/829140370059567104"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 February 8, 2017}}}\par \par \uc2 Senator {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/w/elizabeth_warren/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Elizabeth Warren}}}\uc2 , Democrat of Massachusetts, wrote those \uc2 Twitter\uc2  posts after being halted by the majority leader, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/m/mitch_mcconnell/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Mitch McConnell}}}\uc2  of Kentucky, as she tried to read on the floor a 1986 letter by Coretta Scott King opposing Mr. Sessions\u8217\'20\'19s nomination for a judgeship.\par \par \uc2 Mr. McConnell, in a rare step, said Ms. Warren had {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/republican-senators-vote-to-formally-silence-elizabeth-warren.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 breached Senate rules}}}\uc2  by impugning the character of Mr. Sessions. The Senate then voted, along party lines, to bar Ms. Warren from speaking again during the debate.\par \par \uc2 In the end, though, Democrats can do little more than raise their voices. None of the 52 Republicans have said they would vote against Mr. Sessions, and he needs only a simple majority to win confirmation.\par \par \uc2 In a bit of procedural strategy, Republican leaders held off on Mr. Sessions\u8217\'20\'19s vote until after confirming Betsy DeVos, President Trump\u8217\'20\'19s education secretary. With Mr. Sessions still in the Senate, Republicans had just enough votes to push her to confirmation.\par \par \uc2 A losing case? Blame \u8216\'20\'18politics\u8217\'20\'19\par \par \uc2 A day after a federal appeals court panel {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/trump-immigration-ban-hearing-appeal.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&clickSource=story-heading&module=a-lede-package-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 voiced skepticism}}}\uc2  over his targeted travel ban, Mr. Trump seemed to acknowledge on Wednesday the possibility that he could lose the case.\par \par \uc2 But to lose the normal way, on the merits? The president sees other forces at play.\par \par \uc2 If the U.S. does not win this case as it so obviously should, we can never have the security and safety to which we are entitled. Politics! \u8212\'20\'14 \uc2 Donald J. Trump\uc2  (@realDonaldTrump) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/829299566344359936"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 February 8, 2017}}}\par \par \uc2 Later in the morning, Mr. Trump resumed that theme at a gathering of sheriffs and police chiefs. \u8220\'20\'1CI don\u8217\'20\'19t ever want to call a court biased, so I won\u8217\'20\'19t call it biased,\u8221\'20\'1D he said. \u8220\'20\'1CBut courts seem to be so political.\u8221\'20\'1D He also called the appeals court hearing \u8220\'20\'1Cdisgraceful.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 With that, Mr. Trump kept up his efforts to call into question the independence of the judiciary \u8212\'20\'14 a cornerstone of American democracy. A few days ago, he referred to the district court judge in the travel ban case as a \u8220\'20\'1Cso-called judge.\u8221\'20\'1D And before that, he doubted that the judge in a Trump \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  case could be impartial because of his Mexican heritage.\par \par \uc2 The president has been pre-emptively blaming judges for any terrorist attack that might happen during the travel ban suspension. On Sunday, he attacked the district court judge who blocked his immigration order, James Robart of Seattle. \u8220\'20\'1CIf something happens,\u8221\'20\'1D Mr. Trump wrote on \uc2 Twitter\uc2 , \u8220\'20\'1Cblame him and court system.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 On Wednesday afternoon, Mr. Trump was back on \uc2 Twitter\uc2 , claiming that foreigners were flowing into the United States from \u8220\'20\'1Ccertain areas.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Big increase in traffic into our country from certain areas, while our people are far more vulnerable, as we wait for what should be EASY D! \u8212\'20\'14 \uc2 Donald J. Trump\uc2  (@realDonaldTrump) {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/829384587482656768"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 February 8, 2017}}}\par \par \uc2 Senators want a say before Russia sanctions can be lifted\par \par \uc2 A bipartisan group of senators is expected to introduce legislation on Wednesday that would require congressional approval for Mr. Trump to lift sanctions on Russia, according to two Senate aides.\par \par \uc2 The group is expected to include six senators: \uc2 Lindsey Graham\uc2  of South Carolina, \uc2 John McCain\uc2  of Arizona and \uc2 Marco Rubio\uc2  of Florida, all Republicans; and Benjamin L. Cardin of Maryland, Sherrod Brown of Ohio and Claire McCaskill of Missouri, all Democrats.\par \par \uc2 The effort comes amid longstanding worries on Capitol Hill that the Trump administration might be too dovish on Russia, which intelligence officials say intervened in the election in an effort to help Mr. Trump. Last week, the president seemed to defend the reputation of President \uc2 Vladimir V. Putin\uc2  of Russia by asking an interviewer, \u8220\'20\'1CYou think our country\u8217\'20\'19s so innocent?\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Conservative Jews have a lot to ask the vice president about\par \par \uc2 The vice president will attend a Republican Jewish Coalition gathering in Las Vegas at the end of the month, according to a notice from the group sent to prospective attendees.\par \par \uc2 Las Vegas is home to one of the group\u8217\'20\'19s biggest donors, the casino magnate \uc2 Sheldon G. Adelson\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Mr. Pence\u8217\'20\'19s trip will come a few weeks after the Trump administration issued a muted statement about Israeli settlements, calling for immediate curbs on construction but also signaling a shift away from the Obama administration\u8217\'20\'19s rejection of all settlement activity. It will also come after the president\u8217\'20\'19s promise to immediately move the American Embassy to Jerusalem has been delayed.\par \par \uc2 No walls between Mattis and his Mexican counterparts\par \par \uc2 It seems that no mission is too impossible for \uc2 Jim Mattis\uc2  to take on. During a recent trip to Asia, Mr. Mattis, the defense secretary, succeeded in shoring up connections with South Korea and Japan despite Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s campaign talk about pulling back from the United States\u8217\'20\'19 security commitments in the region.\par \par \uc2 On Tuesday, Mr. Mattis made an effort to salvage relations with Mexico, at least in the area of military cooperation.\par \par \uc2 According to a statement issued Tuesday night by the Pentagon, Mr. Mattis spoke by phone with two of his Mexican counterparts: Gen. Salvador Cienfuegos Zepeda, the secretary of national defense, and Adm. Vidal Francisco Sober\u243\'00\'F3n Sanz, the secretary of the navy. Mr. Mattis talked about the need to strengthen military connections between the two countries, and \u8220\'20\'1Clauded Mexico\u8217\'20\'19s growing leadership in the region,\u8221\'20\'1D the Pentagon said.\par \par \uc2 The statement did not say when Mr. Mattis might be visiting the country, but it noted that Mexico was planning to host the Conference of Defense Ministers of the Americas in 2018. No word if Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s wall will be built by then.\par \par \uc2 Get politics and Washington news updates via {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.facebook.com/nytpolitics"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Facebook}}}\uc2 , {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/nytpolitics"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Twitter}}}\uc2  and in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/morning-briefing"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the Morning Briefing newsletter}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 President Trump on Tuesday at the White House. A vote on his pick for attorney general, Senator Jeff Sessions of Alabama, is expected as soon as Wednesday evening. | Al Drago/The New York Times | Senator Jeff Sessions, center, President Trump\u8217\'20\'19s nominee for attorney general, before a Senate committee meeting on Capitol Hill last week. | Al Drago/The New York Times | President Trump stepped up his criticism of the United States judicial system a day after his travel ban on people from seven Muslim-majority countries faced close scrutiny from an appeals court. | By REUTERS \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170208ed28002s9\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
