\par\par \uc2 Briefing\par {\*\bkmkstart toc37}{\*\bkmkend toc37}\b \uc2 Executive Orders, Betsy DeVos: Your Tuesday Evening Briefing\b0\par\par\uc2 By KAREN ZRAICK and SANDRA STEVENSON \par \uc2 984 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2017\par 16:53\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 (Want to get this briefing by email? Here\u8217\'20\'19s {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/nyt-now-evening-briefing"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the sign-up}}}\uc2 .)\par \par \uc2 Good evening. Here\u8217\'20\'19s the latest.\par \par \uc2 1. A three-judge federal appeals panel {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/trump-immigration-ban-hearing-appeal.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 voiced skepticism}}}\uc2  at the \uc2 U.S. Justice Department\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s broad defense of President Trump\u8217\'20\'19s targeted travel ban.\par \par \uc2 While the case seems destined for the Supreme Court, the appeals court may decide to lift a stay that has offered days of reprieve for refugees and travelers from seven predominantly Muslim countries.\par \par \uc2 Above, a mannequin outside the courthouse was draped in a composite of the flags of the seven countries affected by the ban.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 2. We\u8217\'20\'19ll go back to politics in a minute, but first we want to note: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/02/07/science/earth/antarctic-crack.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Antarctica is cracking}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 A rift in the fourth-largest ice shelf there is growing rapidly \u8212\'20\'14 by about 17 miles in the last two months. A full break, forecast within months, will create one of the largest icebergs ever recorded.\par \par \uc2 Further collapses would allow glaciers to accelerate toward the ocean, where they would melt and cause sea levels to rise.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 3. The Senate {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/betsy-devos-education-secretary-confirmed.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 confirmed Betsy DeVos as education secretary}}}\uc2  after a historic tiebreaking vote from Vice President \uc2 Mike Pence\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Two Republicans voted against Ms. DeVos after tough confirmation hearings, a sign that some members of Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s party are willing to go against him.\par \par \uc2 Our new podcast, The Daily, delves into why Ms. DeVos\u8217\'20\'19s nomination attracted so much controversy. Listen {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://p.nytimes.com/email/re?location=pMJKdIFVI6pghfX2HXfSzxRpdoyDWYNWTiojIldV5/30HM2/ax+2pVLAWRsIZFdVz9cDNp2u4niWrm+AAytQ5VTiWl8MSaLPLbazqy18dJgvOhPOLTIIeWn0dGj2mFPDEC1VHTaSlkd/U1NFFTxrxNHALmudvvC8DiI3rXQDhW9GVypokOY2BssdHtaoYpwDqqP84LmrSWU=&user_id=fb841be9a1ed2e672e395ff2e02515ac&email_type=20170207%20Morning%20Briefing&task_id=1486464452739784&regi_id=0"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 here}}}\uc2  if you\u8217\'20\'19re on a computer, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://p.nytimes.com/email/re?location=pMJKdIFVI6pxqXho0GEqccVIzVFxcX9aV2B4iQBPSXW4Bh1K7tI+8595lu2XuAHe1lHeCYFAXoXPGg5JCXlG9RkMXmzQgEZ4&user_id=fb841be9a1ed2e672e395ff2e02515ac&email_type=20170207%20Morning%20Briefing&task_id=1486464452739784&regi_id=0"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 here}}}\uc2  if you have an iOS device or {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://p.nytimes.com/email/re?location=pMJKdIFVI6qtWOXIIaJ4RdRujFkqVU9pFYKHUpbmEuzLch/5BMLUT7qySAaPygoxuArUvmb4utDoOSyPqCdt46gmAqE/DxIEqbS3hWzfa08g+GaaP5PlceW8SldG2K4EC1nzQ3dyz8bVC4GN+nBV50aduoVUtKIse7Tqxnge356X7CA4nyV4oKhelrOtcJbTxuNhC1EN4TMBb5oRfwPBe1yBbtRqVj3582ANF5Ba5UCN434lHFoxTzLefnubr6EQatFojReAKPJP+/XVb48toViLdelfaoOU&user_id=fb841be9a1ed2e672e395ff2e02515ac&email_type=20170207%20Morning%20Briefing&task_id=1486464452739784&regi_id=0"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 here}}}\uc2  for an Android device.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 4. The White House, arguing that the news media is playing down the threat of terrorism, released a list of 78 terrorist attacks that it says were underreported.\par \par \uc2 It includes dozens of recent attacks that were heavily covered. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/the-white-house-list-of-terror-attacks-underreported-by-media.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Here is the list}}}\uc2 , with links to the coverage.\par \par \uc2 Just as striking was what the White House left off the list: attacks targeting Muslims, who account for the overwhelming majority of victims of Islamist terrorism, and those carried out by non-Muslims, like Dylann S. Roof.\par \par \uc2 Above, an attack in Indonesia last year.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 5. Steve Bannon, the chief adviser to Mr. Trump, has {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/world/europe/vatican-steve-bannon-pope-francis.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 cultivated alliances with traditionalists}}}\uc2  in the Vatican who share his low opinion of \uc2 Pope Francis\uc2  as dangerously misguided, and probably socialist.\par \par \uc2 There is also controversy over China\u8217\'20\'19s participation in a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/world/asia/china-vatican-organ-transplants.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Vatican conference on organ trafficking}}}\uc2 . Critics doubt that the government is keeping its promise to stop harvesting organs from executed prisoners.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 6. Former President \uc2 Barack Obama\uc2  seems to be adjusting to life outside the White House.\par \par \uc2 He and Michelle took a trip to the British Virgin Islands as guests of the business magnate Richard Branson. And {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/politics/obama-kitesurfing-biden-penn.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Mr. Obama learned to kitesurf}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Joe Biden\uc2  took on a new gig at the \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Pennsylvania\uc2 , leading the Penn Biden Center for Diplomacy and Global Engagement.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 7. A Florida man said his motive {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/mosque-fire-florida.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 for setting fire to a mosque}}}\uc2  was anxiety, not hate.\par \par \uc2 Joseph Schreiber was sentenced to 30 years in prison after pleading no contest to starting a fire at the Islamic Center of Fort Pierce on Sept. 11. Omar Mateen, the Orlando nightclub gunman, had occasionally worshiped there.\par \par \uc2 The prosecutor said Mr. Schreiber had told detectives that he believed Muslims were \u8220\'20\'1Ctrying to infiltrate our government\u8221\'20\'1D and that \u8220\'20\'1Cthe teaching of Islam should be completely illegal.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 8. In Hong Kong, a group of urban explorers has found a new answer to relentless construction. They use stealth and drones to create video archives {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/world/asia/hong-kong-historical-preservation.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 of the city\u8217\'20\'19s colonial-era buildings}}}\uc2  before they are razed.\par \par \uc2 One admirer, an architecture professor, said the work was \u8220\'20\'1Cabout forcing us to confront the aesthetic of loss.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 9. Flight attendants are helping to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/us/flight-attendants-human-trafficking.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 fight human trafficking}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 A nonprofit group is training them, and other airport workers, on how to spot people traveling against their will, often young passengers who look disoriented, refuse to make eye contact or act oddly subservient to a traveling companion.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CIt is my responsibility to make sure that these people, whose lives are in my hands while they\u8217\'20\'19re on board my aircraft, are safe,\u8221\'20\'1D one flight attendant said.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 10. \u8220\'20\'1CAdmitting to a sweet tooth these days seems rather illicit, what with sugar cast in the role of Public Enemy No. 1.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 That\u8217\'20\'19s Yotam Ottolenghi, the chef and cookbook author, in his first {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/dining/yotam-ottolenghi-baking-granita-kataifi.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 column on baking and sweets}}}\uc2  for The Times. His cuisine is known for its embrace of vegetables, but he started out as a pastry chef.\par \par \uc2 This week, he offers two recipes that include ingredients not usually associated with dessert: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1018574-pastry-nests-with-poached-pears-and-feta-and-saffron-cream"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 pastry nests with poached pears and feta and saffron cream}}}\uc2 , and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://cooking.nytimes.com/recipes/1018575-pomegranate-and-rose-granita"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 pomegranate and rose granita}}}\uc2  with rose petals.\par \par \uc2 _____\par \par \uc2 11. Finally, our TV reporter is trying something new: a roundup of the best jokes, skits and interviews on late-night comedy shows. In the first installment, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/arts/television/jimmy-kimmel-jimmy-fallon-stephen-colbert.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 comedians took on the Super Bowl}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 You need sleep, after all, and something in the news to smile about.\par \par \uc2 Photographs may appear out of order for some readers. Viewing {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://mobile.nytimes.com/2017/02/07/briefing/executive-orders-betsy-devos.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 this version of the briefing}}}\uc2  should help.\par \par \uc2 Your Evening Briefing is posted at 6 p.m. Eastern.\par \par \uc2 And don\u8217\'20\'19t miss Your Morning Briefing, posted weekdays at 6 a.m. Eastern, and Your Weekend Briefing, posted at 6 a.m. Sundays.\par \par \uc2 Want to look back? Here\u8217\'20\'19s {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/briefing/new-england-patriots-elizabeth-ii.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 last night\u8217\'20\'19s briefing}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 What did you like? What do you want to see here? Let us know at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:briefing@nytimes.com?subject=Evening%20Briefing%20Feedback"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 briefing@nytimes.com}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/briefing/new-england-patriots-elizabeth-ii.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 New England Patriots, Elizabeth II: Your Monday Evening Briefing}}}\par \par \uc2 Jim Wilson/The New York Times | The New York Times | Michael Reynolds/European Pressphoto Agency | Xinhua, via Agence France-Presse \u8212\'20\'14 Getty Images | Alessandro Bianchi/Reuters | Virgin, via Reuters | St. Lucie County Sheriff's Office, via Reuters | Lam Yik Fei for The New York Times | Ruth Fremson/The New York Times | Rikki Snyder for The New York Times | ABC \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170207ed27008hm\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
