\par\par \uc2 Fashion & Style\par {\*\bkmkstart toc39}{\*\bkmkend toc39}\b \uc2 After Two Tragedies, a Love to Bring Down Barriers\b0\par\par\uc2 By PENELOPE GREEN \par \uc2 1,037 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2017\par 05:57\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 Correction Appended\par \par \uc2 When Marian Wright and \uc2 Peter Edelman\uc2  married in July 1968, their wedding was like an armistice. In April, the Rev. Dr. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/k/martin_luther_jr_king/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Martin Luther King Jr.}}}\uc2  had been assassinated; two months later, Senator {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/people/k/robert_francis_kennedy/index.html?inline=nyt-per"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Robert F. Kennedy}}}\uc2  was murdered \u8212\'20\'14 on June 6, Mrs. Edelman\u8217\'20\'19s birthday. For years afterward, the couple would spend that day at Arlington Cemetery. The national tragedies were personal for the couple: Mrs. Edelman had worked for Dr. King, and Mr. Edelman had been an aide to the senator.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1968/07/15/77094092.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times covered the wedding as a news story}}}\uc2 , sending Nan Robertson, then a reporter for the paper\u8217\'20\'19s Washington bureau. The ceremony was held on the lawn at the home of their friend, Adam Walinsky, a speechwriter for Senator Kennedy, in McLean, Va. The choice to marry in Virginia was deliberate: A year earlier, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1967/06/13/98368288.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 the state\u8217\'20\'19s law against interracial marriage had been struck down}}}\uc2  in a suit brought by Richard and Mildred Loving. The Edelmans were the third interracial couple to marry there after the Lovings prevailed.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CI hate barriers,\u8221\'20\'1D Mrs. Edelman said. \u8220\'20\'1CAnd it was a time to bring down barriers.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Theirs was a kind of royal wedding, the beginning of one of the most notable partnerships of the civil rights era and beyond. Mrs. Edelman would soon found the \uc2 Children\u8217\'20\'19s Defense Fund\uc2 , now in its 43rd year. She would also hire a young Hillary Rodham, just out of law school.\par \par \uc2 Now a professor at Georgetown \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Mr. Edelman would continue to work in law and policy. He was a high official at the \uc2 Department of Health and Human Services\uc2  during \uc2 Bill Clinton\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s first term as president. In 1996, the Edelman-Clinton friendship would publicly sour when President Clinton signed the welfare reform act of 1996; Mr. Edelman resigned in protest, and both he and Mrs. Edelman wrote articles denouncing the law. Yet in November it was at a \uc2 Children\u8217\'20\'19s Defense Fund\uc2  dinner where {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/17/us/politics/hillary-clinton-in-emotional-speech-implores-supporters-to-keep-believing-in-america.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Mrs.}}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/17/us/politics/hillary-clinton-in-emotional-speech-implores-supporters-to-keep-believing-in-america.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  Clinton made her first public appearance after conceding the election}}}\uc2 , to thank her mentor for a lifetime of inspiration. \u8220\'20\'1CIf there\u8217\'20\'19s anyone who knows how to pick yourself up and get back on your feet and get back to work,\u8221\'20\'1D she said, \u8220\'20\'1Cit is Marian.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 In spring 1967, Mrs. Edelman was a 28-year-old civil rights lawyer, the first African-American woman admitted to the Mississippi bar, a liaison to Dr. King\u8217\'20\'19s Southern Christian Leadership Conference, an organizer at Head Start and counsel for Dr. King\u8217\'20\'19s Poor People\u8217\'20\'19s Campaign. She had testified before a Senate subcommittee on how the War on Poverty was working in the Southern States, and had invited the senators to come see for themselves.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Edelman, then 29, was sent ahead to Jackson, Miss., where her law offices were, to plan the trip for Senator Kennedy. She took his phone call, but said she was too busy writing a brief to meet in person. \u8220\'20\'1CBut you\u8217\'20\'19ve got to eat dinner!\u8221\'20\'1D Mr. Edelman insisted, and she relented.\par \par \uc2 She was Southern born, educated at Spelman College in Atlanta and at Yale Law School; he was from Minnesota, a Harvard man. After dinner, they talked until midnight.\par \par \uc2 What Senator Kennedy would see on that trip would change history: ragged, starving children; babies too malnourished to move; the hollow faces of the hungry poor all through the Mississippi Delta, too destitute to pay the $2 a day that food stamps then cost. Now the program is free.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CI couldn\u8217\'20\'19t think of a better time to have grown up,\u8221\'20\'1D Mrs. Edelman said. \u8220\'20\'1CI feel so lucky.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 The Edelmans faced none of the struggles of the Lovings, she added. \u8220\'20\'1CIt was another era. We were past that time.\u8221\'20\'1D Their challenges were more quotidian: balancing work and family.\par \par \uc2 The couple have three sons. Jonah Edelman and Joshua Edelman are education advocates; Ezra Edelman is a director and producer, whose most recent film is \u8220\'20\'1CO.J.: Made in America,\u8221\'20\'1D the nearly eight-hour documentary that {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://oscar.go.com/nominees/documentary-feature/o-j-made-in-america"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 was recently nominated for an Oscar}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CI\u8217\'20\'19m so proud of them,\u8221\'20\'1D Mrs. Edelman said. \u8220\'20\'1CI\u8217\'20\'19m most proud I kept them out of law school.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Mr. Edelman said, \u8220\'20\'1CI don\u8217\'20\'19t agree with that!\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CGood marriages are hard to develop and maintain,\u8221\'20\'1D Mrs. Edelman said. \u8220\'20\'1CWe got married when the roles of men and women were changing, and I moved with Peter twice. How do you nurture your professional passions while trying to make sure you\u8217\'20\'19re good parents? If I had any advice to give, I\u8217\'20\'19d say:, \u8216\'20\'18Try not to be a superwoman, and try to be honest. Talk to each other in ways you can be heard and not be angry.\u8217\'20\'19\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 As for the wedding announcement, Mrs. Edelman said she was stunned to see it in the paper. \u8220\'20\'1CI don\u8217\'20\'19t remember Nan being there. And there\u8217\'20\'19s one mistake. It was my brother, Harry Wright, who escorted me, not my brother-in-law.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 It\u8217\'20\'19s probably too late to issue a correction.\par \par \uc2 Continue following our fashion and lifestyle coverage on \uc2 Facebook\uc2  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.facebook.com/nytimesstyles"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Styles}}}\uc2  and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.facebook.com/modernlove"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Modern Love}}}\uc2 ), \uc2 Twitter\uc2  ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/nytstyles"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Styles}}}\uc2 , {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/nytfashion"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Fashion}}}\uc2  and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/nytimesvows"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Weddings}}}\uc2 ) and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://instagram.com/nytimesfashion"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Instagram}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Penelope Green is a Styles reporter at The New York Times.\par \par \uc2 Correction: February 7, 2017, Tuesday\par \par \uc2 This article has been revised to reflect the following correction: An earlier version of this article misstated the location of Marian Wright Edelman\u8217\'20\'19s office in 1967. It was in Jackson, Miss., not Cleveland, Miss. We also misstated \uc2 Peter Edelman\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s role with the \uc2 Department of Health and Human Services\uc2 . He was a high official, not counsel. Further, Marian Wright Edelman was a liaison to Dr. King, not a congressional liaison.\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/17/us/politics/hillary-clinton-in-emotional-speech-implores-supporters-to-keep-believing-in-america.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Hillary Clinton, in Emotional Speech, Implores Supporters to Keep Believing in America}}}\par \par \uc2 * {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2017/01/31/fashion/eleanor-roosevelt-wedding-announcement.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The Roosevelts\u8217\'20\'19 Wedding Announcement, Annotated}}}\par \par \uc2 The Edelmans were the third interracial couple to be married in Virginia. | Capitol and Glogau | The Edelmans were the third interracial couple to marry in Virginia. | Capitol and Glogau | The Edelmans at their home in Washington. | Doug Mills/The New York Times | Theirs was a kind of royal wedding, the beginning of one of the most notable partnerships of the civil rights era and beyond. | Capitol and Glogau \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170207ed27003ml\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
