\par\par \uc2 California Today\par \uc2 U.S.\par {\*\bkmkstart toc43}{\*\bkmkend toc43}\b \uc2 California Today: Granddaughter of Cesar Chavez Comes Home\b0\par\par\uc2 By MIKE McPHATE \par \uc2 1,179 \uc2 words\par \uc2 7 February 2017\par 07:01\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 Good morning.\par \par \uc2 (Want to get California Today by email? {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/california-today"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  Here\u8217\'20\'19s the sign-up }}}\uc2  .)\par \par \uc2 A couple of months ago, then Senator-elect Kamala Harris appointed Julie Chavez Rodriguez to be her state director, overseeing operations in California.\par \par \uc2 Ms. Rodriguez, 38, would \u8220\'20\'1Cgive voice to our vulnerable communities,\u8221\'20\'1D {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.harris.senate.gov/content/senator-elect-kamala-harris-announces-appointment-julie-chavez-rodriguez-california-state"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Ms. Harris said at the time}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Ms. Rodriguez had experience. Her most recent job was in the White House serving as senior deputy director of public engagement and special assistant to President \uc2 Barack Obama\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 But she also brought a personal connection to politics \u8212\'20\'14 she is the granddaughter of Cesar Chavez, the great labor leader for farmworkers.\par \par \uc2 Raised in the Central Valley, Ms. Rodriguez was surrounded by activism. Once, at age 9, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://madisoncourier.com/Content/News/News/Article/Born-into-a-life-of-helping-others/178/961/61938"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 she was arrested}}}\uc2  during a protest outside a supermarket while distributing fliers about pesticide risks.\par \par \uc2 Ever since, those battles have shaped her path, she said.\par \par \uc2 We caught up with Ms. Rodriguez by phone. Some excerpts from the conversation:\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Tell me about your gig. What have you been up to?\par \par \uc2 Where do I begin? I think obviously building out our team here, making sure that we have a staff that really reflects the face of California.\par \par \uc2 \u8230\'20\'26 More recently, we\u8217\'20\'19ve been dealing with a lot of constituents\u8217\'20\'19 requests and services that came as a result of the executive orders that we saw from the administration around immigrants and refugees and what we\u8217\'20\'19ve seen in the context of the travel ban. So we\u8217\'20\'19ve been dealing with a lot of casework in that area as well.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 What are you hearing from unauthorized immigrants in the state? And what are you telling them?\par \par \uc2 I think that there is a tremendous amount of growing concern and fear in particular among immigrant communities. I think what the senator has been able to do and what we\u8217\'20\'19ve been able to do here in the state in the short amount of time that we\u8217\'20\'19ve actually been in office is show that she will continue to be a voice for them and for the state of California.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 What do you think your grandfather would make of all this?\par \par \uc2 I try not to speak for him too often. But I think given the work that he did over the course of his lifetime and given the role that he played to shed light on the inhumane treatment of farmworkers that he himself experienced, I think that he would really call into question the lack of humanity in a lot of both the rhetoric as well as the policies that we\u8217\'20\'19re seeing coming out of this current administration.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 You were in Washington for more than seven years. How is it coming back to California?\par \par \uc2 I am so excited to be back in my home state. And in case you can\u8217\'20\'19t hear my smile through the phone, it is an ear-to-ear grin. Both in terms of the increase in vitamin D that I will be receiving on a daily basis, but in all seriousness being able to come back to a state that has helped to make me who I am.\par \par \uc2 California Online\par \par \uc2 (Please note: We regularly highlight articles on news sites that have limited access for nonsubscribers.)\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 After President Trump\u8217\'20\'19s immigration ban, employees (not executives) pushed Silicon Valley to go full-tilt political. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/business/trump-travel-ban-apple-google-facebook.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Democrats went after Mr. Trump for calling California \u8220\'20\'1Cout of control.\u8221\'20\'1D They noted the state\u8217\'20\'19s massive economy. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ww2.kqed.org/news/2017/02/06/california-democrats-counter-trumps-threat-to-defund-the-state/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The Associated Press}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Tensions have flared between Mr. Trump and Mexico\u8217\'20\'19s leader. But the mayors of San Diego and Tijuana are reaffirming ties. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/border-baja-california/sd-me-tijuana-mayors-20170206-story.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 San Diego Union-Tribune}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The Ninth Circuit in San Francisco is set to rule on Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s travel ban. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/us/politics/trump-travel-ban-court.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 A \uc2 U.C. Berkeley\uc2  evolutionary biologist declared his intention to run for the Senate. His slogan: \u8220\'20\'1CLiberty, Equality, Reality.\u8221\'20\'1D [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/science/donald-trump-scientists-politics.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 California Republicans are asking the Trump administration to block funding for the bullet train. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/local/california/la-me-bullet-train-trump-20170206-story.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Los Angeles Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Remember the BART janitor who earned $270,000 a year? A television crew caught him spending hours inside a closet. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ktvu.com/news/2-investigates/234011066-story"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 KTVU}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Kyle Shanahan was hired as the 49ers coach. His mission: restore a franchise that\u8217\'20\'19s won five Super Bowls. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sfchronicle.com/49ers/article/It-s-official-49ers-announce-hiring-of-Kyle-10912733.php"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 San Francisco Chronicle}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The H ollywood Reporter\u8217\'20\'19s top editor, Janice Min, is leaving, which may foreshadow its sale. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/06/business/janice-min-hollywood-reporter.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 David Axelrod, a Los Angeles composer whose work was sampled in some of hip-hop\u8217\'20\'19s biggest hits, has died. He was 83. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/music/la-et-ms-david-axelrod-musician-dies-20170206-story.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Los Angeles Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Video: A colony of 15,000 Monarch butterflies returned to Pismo Beach. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sanluisobispo.com/news/local/article131008379.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 San Luis Tribune}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 And Finally ...\par \par \uc2 Mayor Ed Lee announced Monday that San Francisco\u8217\'20\'19s main community college would be tuition free for city residents.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CWhen our city works together we can accomplish great things,\u8221\'20\'1D {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/mayoredlee/status/828712197802954752"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 he said}}}\uc2  during a news conference.\par \par \uc2 To pay the cost to City College of San Francisco, the city will draw from the increase of a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://ballotpedia.org/San_Francisco,_California,_Real_Estate_Transfer_Tax_Increase,_Proposition_W_(November_2016)"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 real estate transfer tax}}}\uc2  that voters approved in November.\par \par \uc2 Lately, California has seen {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/14/us/california-today-community-colleges-free-tuition.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 a spike}}}\uc2  in programs offering support to community college students, propelled in part by a nationwide push to improve access to higher education.\par \par \uc2 In November, a coalition of education leaders in the San Joaquin Valley {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.fresnobee.com/news/local/education/article112156357.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 introduced an initiative}}}\uc2  that would provide a free semester of community college to students who meet certain academic goals.\par \par \uc2 City College of San Francisco, founded in 1935, serves about 60,000 students. Until now, course costs for city residents have run {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.ccsf.edu/en/student-services/admissions-and-registration/registration/tuition-and-fees.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 $46 a unit}}}\uc2 , or roughly $1,100 a year.\par \par \uc2 Even with that expense waived, students will still have to figure out their living costs. In San Francisco, that\u8217\'20\'19s {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.collegecalc.org/colleges/california/city-college-of-san-francisco/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 no small order}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 California Today goes live at 6 a.m. Pacific time weekdays. Tell us what you want to see: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:CAtoday@nytimes.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 CAtoday@nytimes.com}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The California Today columnist, Mike McPhate, is a third-generation Californian \u8212\'20\'14 born outside Sacramento and raised in San Juan Capistrano. He lives in Davis. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/mmcphate"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Follow him on Twitter}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 California Today is edited by Julie Bloom, who grew up in Los Angeles and attended \uc2 U.C. Berkeley\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Julie Chavez Rodriguez at the main office for Senator Kamala Harris\u8217\'20\'19s California team in downtown Los Angeles on Monday. | Andrew Cullen for The New York Times | A protest outside Google\u8217\'20\'19s headquarters in Mountain View last month. Google and other Silicon Valley companies said that a ban on visitors from seven largely Muslim countries could hurt the economy. | Jason Henry for The New York Times | Michael Eisen in his lab at the \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of California in Berkeley. Dr. Eisen registered the Twitter handle @SenatorPhD and declared his intention to run in the 2018 election for a seat in the United States Senate. | Jason Henry for The New York Times | Janice Min with Matthew Belloni, who will take over as the top editor at The Hollywood Reporter when she steps down at the end of February. | Monica Almeida/The New York Times | City College of San Francisco\u8217\'20\'19s Science Hall. | Noah Berger for The New York Times \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170207ed270040i\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
