p runners rehabilitate from injuries to that joint.\par \par \uc2 But there is a literal downside. People often trip, stumble or slam into objects and other people while running backward. As a 2015 study diplomatically concluded, backward running results in ''a higher magnitude of coordination variability'' than forward running.\par \par \uc2 On balance, though, the benefits can outweigh the risks, says Giovanni Cavagna, an emeritus professor of physiology at the \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Milan in Italy, who led the 2011 study.\par \par \uc2 ''Backward running allows training without repetitive pounding,'' he says.\par \par \uc2 Best to try it first on a running track, he suggests, or with a forward-running partner who can point out obstacles.\par \par \uc2 This is a more complete version of the story than the one that appeared in print.\par \par \uc2 (PHOTOGRAPH BY FABRICE COFFRINI/AFP/GETTY IMAGES) \par \par \uc2 Document NYTF000020170207ed270003c\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw284\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4260\pichgoal600
