\par\par \uc2 California Today\par \uc2 U.S.\par {\*\bkmkstart toc72}{\*\bkmkend toc72}\b \uc2 California Today: Tackling Los Angeles\u8217\'20\'19s Deadly Smog\b0\par\par\uc2 By MIKE McPHATE \par \uc2 1,125 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 February 2017\par 06:47\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 Good morning.\par \par \uc2 (Want to get California Today by email? {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/newsletters/california-today"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  Here\u8217\'20\'19s the sign-up }}}\uc2  .)\par \par \uc2 More than 1,300 lives are cut short each year in the Los Angeles area because of air pollution, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.healthoftheair.org/download-full-report"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 scientists say}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Now, after years of work, regulators are getting ready to adopt their most substantial plan in more than a decade to do something about it.\par \par \uc2 The proposal is outlined in 5,000-plus pages from the South Coast Air Quality Management District, whose jurisdiction extends across Los Angeles, Orange, Riverside and San Bernardino Counties.\par \par \uc2 Not surprisingly, it has set off debate, as critics have called the plan too lenient on industry.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CCalifornia has made clear that it intends to be a leader on environmental issues,\u8221\'20\'1D said Angela Johnson Meszaros, a staff attorney with \uc2 Earthjustice\uc2 , an environmental law group. \u8220\'20\'1CAnd here we\u8217\'20\'19ve got the Los Angeles air agency not doing all that it can.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 All sides recognize that industries under the agency\u8217\'20\'19s regulatory power \u8212\'20\'14 including refineries, ports and warehouses \u8212\'20\'14 must adopt cleaner technologies.\par \par \uc2 The agreement breaks down over how to get there.\par \par \uc2 The draft blueprint would adopt some tougher emissions rules. But it also calls for a carrot approach: roughly $15 billion in handouts over the next 15 years to encourage polluters to clean up.\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://iecn.com/letter-scaqmd-inland-empire-leadership/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Some community leaders have portrayed}}}\uc2  the incentives \u8212\'20\'14 which would surely involve tax increases \u8212\'20\'14 as a form of corporate welfare at the expense of low-income families.\par \par \uc2 But {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dailynews.com/opinion/20170202/much-reviewed-air-quality-plan-should-be-passed-now-guest-commentary"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 supporters of the plan}}}\uc2  have argued that they are needed to avoid stifling business. Smaller operators, for example, may not be able to afford a new, cleaner truck.\par \par \uc2 \u8220\'20\'1CObviously you can\u8217\'20\'19t make everybody happy,\u8221\'20\'1D said Philip M. Fine, deputy executive officer for the air district. \u8220\'20\'1CBut we think we\u8217\'20\'19ve developed a sensible, comprehensive and regulatory approach.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 At a public meeting last Friday, the air agency\u8217\'20\'19s board was supposed to vote on a final version of the plan.\par \par \uc2 Hundreds of people showed up, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/SouthCoastAQMD/status/827601359872552960"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 filling overflow rooms}}}\uc2 . Testimony included stories of the personal toll that asthma is taking on young Californians. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dailybreeze.com/opinion/20170202/much-reviewed-air-quality-plan-should-be-passed-now-guest-commentary"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Business leaders}}}\uc2  warned of job losses if the plan were amended to add new rules.\par \par \uc2 In the end, the board postponed the vote, citing the unexpected absence of a member. They\u8217\'20\'19ll try again next month.\par \par \uc2 California Online\par \par \uc2 (Please note: We regularly highlight articles on news sites that have limited access for nonsubscribers.)\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \u8220\'20\'1CCalifornia in many ways is out of control,\u8221\'20\'1D President Trump said in an interview with Bill O\u8217\'20\'19Reilly. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sacbee.com/news/politics-government/article130942769.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Sacramento Bee}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s refugee actions have reverberated in San Diego, a longtime hub for the nation\u8217\'20\'19s new arrivals. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.sandiegouniontribune.com/news/immigration/sd-me-refugee-hub-20170202-story.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 San Diego Union-Tribune}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 In a dorm at \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of California, Merced, undocumented students bond over their hopes and fears. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/education/edlife/daca-undocumented-university-of-california-merced-fiat-lux-scholars.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Milo Yiannopoulos, whose speech at \uc2 U.C. Berkeley\uc2  was canceled after protests, said he planned to try again. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.dailycal.org/2017/02/04/milo-yiannopoulos-announces-intention-reschedule-campus-talk/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Daily Californian}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Californians are using less electricity. Some power plants have even shut down. So why do state officials keep approving new ones? [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.latimes.com/projects/la-fi-electricity-capacity/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Los Angeles Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The Anaheim White House restaurant is known for helping needy children. Now, after it was damaged by fire, donations are pouring in. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ocregister.com/articles/serato-743207-saturday-children.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Orange County Register}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Marta Becket died at 92. A New York ballerina and Broadway dancer, she created a cultural institution in the Mojave Desert. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/arts/dance/marta-becket-dead.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Airbnb\uc2 , one of the most aggressive corporate critics of Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s immigration policy, took its opposition to the Super Bowl. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/technology/airbnb-super-bowl-ad-trump-travel-ban.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Tech companies say the H-1B program is needed to find highly skilled employees. But it has also been used to cut jobs. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/h-1b-visa-tech-cheers-for-foreign-workers.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Mavericks, a top big-wave surfing event, was canceled after organizers filed for bankruptcy. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/sports/titans-of-mavericks-big-wave-surfing-bankruptcy.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 In Bel Air, the most expensive house in the nation is on the market for $250 million, but one is rising nearby that may cost half a billion. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/03/business/americas-most-expensive-house-times-two.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \u8220\'20\'1CBuilding the Wall,\u8221\'20\'1D a response to the Trump era, took just a week to write. A Los Angeles theater will mount the play next month. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/theater/trump-wall-mexico-play.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \u8220\'20\'1CThis Is Us\u8221\'20\'1D is the biggest hit for the broadcast networks since \u8220\'20\'1CEmpire.\u8221\'20\'1D [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/media/this-is-us-nbc-tv-mandy-moore-milo-ventimiglia.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 The New York Times}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 Photos: \uc2 Tom Brady\uc2  during his days as a high school quarterback in San Mateo. [{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Tom-Brady-High-School-Photos-Serra-San-Mateo-412455253.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 NBC Bay Area}}}\uc2 ]\par \par \uc2 Coming Up This Week\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.attpbgolf.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 AT&T Pebble Beach Pro-Am}}}\uc2  kicks off Thursday. Among the pros: Jordan Spieth, Dustin Johnson and the No. 1-ranked Jason Day. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.mercurynews.com/2017/01/24/bill-murray-scheduled-to-play-this-years-att-pebble-beach-pro-am/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Bill Murray}}}{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.mercurynews.com/2017/01/24/bill-murray-scheduled-to-play-this-years-att-pebble-beach-pro-am/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2  will join}}}\uc2  the celebrity field.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The Imperial Valley town of Holtville, the self-proclaimed carrot capital of the world, holds its 70th annual {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.holtvillechamber.org/carrot-festival"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Carrot Festival}}}\uc2  all week. The theme: \u8220\'20\'1CWe dig carrots.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 On Saturday, San Francisco hosts its annual {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.chineseparade.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Chinese New Year parade}}}\uc2 . The nighttime celebration will usher in the Year of the Rooster with floats and firecrackers.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.grammy.com/"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Grammy Awards}}}\uc2  are Sunday. An all-star musical tribute to Prince is expected to be among the memorable moments.\par \par \uc2 And Finally ...\par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.parks.ca.gov/?page_id=578"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 McWay Falls}}}\uc2  is among the most photographed of Big Sur\u8217\'20\'19s vistas.\par \par \uc2 For obvious reason \u8212\'20\'14 the falls tumble 80 feet off a granite cliff into an almost impossibly beautiful cove.\par \par \uc2 Hajer Dlame, 26, a reader from the Bay Area, shared a photo she snapped at sunset while visiting with her mother last month.\par \par \uc2 Alas, the beach itself, part of a state park, is strictly off limits. Visitors are confined to a nearby trail.\par \par \uc2 The upside is McWay Cove has remained an unspoiled slice of the California coast.\par \par \uc2 Want to submit a photo for possible publication? {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/01/04/us/california-today-reader-photos.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 You can do it here}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 California Today goes live at 6 a.m. Pacific time weekdays. Tell us what you want to see: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "mailto:CAtoday@nytimes.com"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 CAtoday@nytimes.com}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 The California Today columnist, Mike McPhate, is a third-generation Californian \u8212\'20\'14 born outside Sacramento and raised in San Juan Capistrano. He lives in Davis. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/mmcphate"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Follow him on Twitter}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 California Today is edited by Julie Bloom, who grew up in Los Angeles and attended \uc2 U.C. Berkeley\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Los Angeles is draped in some of the country\u8217\'20\'19s worst air pollution. | Mark Rolston/Agence France-Presse \u8212\'20\'14 Getty Images | Madely Martinez, Juan Robles and Cruzangel Nava, all undocumented, are housemates in Tenaya Hall, a dorm for low-income, first-generation students at the \b \highlight22