\par\par \uc2 Business Day; DealBook\par {\*\bkmkstart toc74}{\*\bkmkend toc74}\b \uc2 Morning Agenda: Trump\u8217\'20\'19s Immigration Order, (Modest) Diversity Gains\b0\par\par\uc2 By AMIE TSANG \par \uc2 771 \uc2 words\par \uc2 6 February 2017\par 04:49\par \uc2 NYTimes.com Feed\par \uc2 NYTFEED\par \uc2 English\par \uc2 Copyright 2017. The New York Times Company. All Rights Reserved. \par \par \uc2 The confrontation over President Trump\u8217\'20\'19s ban on refugees and visitors from several predominantly Muslim countries reached the courts at the weekend, foreshadowing the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/us/politics/donald-trump-mike-pence-travel-ban-judge.html?hp&action=click&pgtype=Homepage&clickSource=story-heading&module=first-column-region&region=top-news&WT.nav=top-news"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 years of legal battles}}}\uc2  that could lie ahead for the administration.\par \par \uc2 The ban was blocked at a Federal District Court in Seattle and an appeals court in California refused to reinstate it. The government was instead ordered to file a brief defending Mr. Trump\u8217\'20\'19s order.\par \par \uc2 That is not the only immigration issue that is in the headlines.\par \par \uc2 Debate over the use of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/h-1b-visa-tech-cheers-for-foreign-workers.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 H-1B visas}}}\uc2  has also been simmering as employers prepare for Mr. Trump to sign an executive order to overhaul the program.\par \par \uc2 H-1B visas are intended to bring in foreign professionals with college degrees and specialized skills to fill jobs when qualified Americans cannot be found. There could be as many as a million H-1B visa holders residing in the United States, accounting for up to 13 percent of jobs in the technology sector alone.\par \par \uc2 A draft on an executive order leaked last week showed that options for modifying the program would be considered to \u8220\'20\'1Censure that the beneficiaries of the program are the best and the brightest.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 Critics say that American companies are gaming the system to snap up visas so that they can replace American workers with cheaper, temporary staff members. But proponents of the H-1B say it is an important way to attract top talent to the country.\par \par \uc2 The status of the immigrants protected by the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals program is also {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/dealbook/wells-fargo-student-loan-illegal-immigrants.html?ref=dealbook"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 a source of concern}}}\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Many of these people are worried that they will lose the protections that allowed hundreds of thousands of people taken to the United States as children to obtain jobs, pursue college degrees and live openly in the country where they were raised.\par \par \uc2 They already face difficulties in completing their education. One of these people, Mitzie Perez, is trying to challenge policies that make it difficult for undocumented students to finance higher education with a lawsuit seeking class-action status.\par \par \uc2 The subject of immigration even featured at the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/media/commercials-super-bowl-51.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Super Bowl}}}\uc2 :\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Airbnb\uc2 \u8217\'20\'19s advertisement said, \u8220\'20\'1CWe believe no matter who you are, where you\u8217\'20\'19re from, who you love or who you worship, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/technology/airbnb-super-bowl-ad-trump-travel-ban.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 we all belong}}}\uc2 . The world is more beautiful the more you accept.\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Coca-Cola\uc2  revived an ad from the 2014 {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://topics.nytimes.com/top/reference/timestopics/subjects/s/super_bowl/index.html?inline=nyt-classifier"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Super Bowl}}}\uc2 , which featured people singing a multilingual version of \u8220\'20\'1C{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/super-bowl-commercials-politics.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 America the Beautiful}}}\uc2 .\u8221\'20\'1D\par \par \uc2 At the same time, the unwinding of government regulations put in place during the Obama administration continues apace.\par \par \uc2 Ajit Pai, the chairman of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/technology/trumps-fcc-quickly-targets-net-neutrality-rules.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Federal Communications Commission}}}\uc2 , stopped nine companies from providing high-speed interest service at a discount to low-income individuals. He also withdrew an effort to keep prison phone rates down and scrapped a proposal to break open the cable box market, as part of a flurry of actions last week, many of which were not publicly announced.\par \par \uc2 Consumer advocacy groups and telecoms analysts were stunned. The message was: the F.C.C., an independent agency, will mirror the Trump administration\u8217\'20\'19s rollback of government regulations.\par \par \uc2 Modest Gains for Diversity\par \par \uc2 The proportion of women and minorities on the board seats of Fortune 500 companies has increased (a little), but most of the positions are {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/05/business/dealbook/fortune-500-board-directors-diversity.html?ref=business"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 still held by white men}}}\uc2 , according to the Alliance for Board Diversity and Deloitte.\par \par \uc2 Why aren\u8217\'20\'19t more women and minorities on these boards?\par \par \uc2 Companies still turn to people with chief executive experience and these tend to be men. There is also little turnover in board seats, so change is unlikely to come quickly.\par \par \uc2 One possible bright spot: many board members are in their 70s and likely to step down in the coming years, opening up seats to more diverse members.\par \par \uc2 Coming Up\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 The \uc2 International Monetary Fund\uc2  will hold a board meeting to discuss whether it will participate in Greece\u8217\'20\'19s current bailout program. It must reach an agreement with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/25/business/international/greece-debt-relief-imf-eurozone-bailout.html"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 Greece\u8217\'20\'19s European creditors}}}\uc2  over debt calculations and austerity conditions by Feb. 20, when European finance ministers meet in Brussels to review the program.\par \par \uc2 \u8226\'20\'22 \uc2 Mario Draghi\uc2 , the president of the European Central Bank, will speak to members of the \uc2 European Parliament\uc2 . He is expected to face questions about what the Trump presidency means for the eurozone and whether rising inflation rates will prompt the central bank to begin withdrawing its economic stimulus measures.\par \par \uc2 Follow Amie Tsang on \uc2 Twitter\uc2  @amietsang.\par \par \uc2 Hank Nguyen, Audrey Hatten-Milholin and Margaret Horn lost their jobs at \b \highlight22\uc2 University\b0 \highlight\uc2  of California, San Francisco. | Jason Henry for The New York Times \par \par \uc2 Document NYTFEED020170206ed26002xl\par }\page {\par\fs20{\*\shppict{\pict\pngblip\picw300\pich40\picscaley100\picscalex100\picwgoal4500\pichgoal600
